description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:624-641

When parsing POSITION_SATS_IN_VIEW_FIELD and POSITION_PRECISION_BITS_FIELD:
  case POSITION_SATS_IN_VIEW_FIELD:
      if (wt != PB_WT_VARINT || pb_read_varint(&cur, &v) < 0) {
          return -EINVAL;
      }
      if (v <= UINT8_MAX) {
          position->satellites = (uint8_t)v;
          position->satellites_valid = true;
      }
      break;

If v > UINT8_MAX (255), the field is silently ignored. No error, no warning. The message is still parsed successfully.

This could mask data corruption or protocol misuse. A satellites count > 255 is physically impossible, but the silent ignore makes debugging harder.

Consider:
1. Logging a warning (if debug enabled)
2. Setting an 'out of range' flag for diagnostics
3. Or documenting this behavior explicitly
